A confirmed Samba exploitation attempt was detected against Metasploitable2 from IP 192.168.1.101. Alerts were generated by Wazuh and validated through correlated log analysis.
Immediate containment actions were taken by isolating the affected VM and blocking the attacker IP using CrowdSec. Due to confirmed exploitation and potential post-exploitation risk,
the incident was escalated to Tier 2 for deeper forensic analysis and remediation planning.
